1 olive oil
1 carrot
1 white turnip
1 tin lentils
1 Brown Onion
½ lemon
1 packet roasted almonds
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
20 g butter
1 tsp honey
1 tbs balsamic vinegar
1 tsp brown sugar
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 packet couscous
1 packet tahini
1 packet Garlic Dip
1 packet baby spinach leaves
1 bag herbs
½ tbs water (for the onion)
¾ cup water (for the couscous)

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Cut carrot into thick half-moons. Peel white
turnip, then cut into small chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with
olive oil, then season with salt and pepper.
Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast until
tender, 20-25 minutes.

• While the veggies are roasting, drain and rinse
lentils. Thinly slice onion. Slice lemon into
wedges. Roughly chop roasted almonds.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium heat. Cook lentils and chermoula
spice blend until fragrant and warmed through,
1-2 minutes.
• Add the butter and honey and cook, stirring,
until melted, 1 minute. Transfer to a bowl.

• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with
a drizzle of olive oil. Cook onion, stirring, until
softened, 5-6 minutes.
• Reduce the heat to medium, then add the
balsamic vinegar, water (for the onion) and
brown sugar and mix well. Cook until dark and
sticky, 3-5 minutes. Set aside.

• While the onion is cooking, add water (for the
couscous) and vegetable stock powder to a
medium saucepan. Bring to the boil.
• Add couscous and stir to combine. Cover with a
lid and remove from heat. Set aside until water is
absorbed, 5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork.

• In a small bowl, combine tahini and garlic dip.
Set aside.
• Add the lentils, roasted veggies, baby spinach
leaves and a drizzle of olive oil to the couscous.
Toss to combine.

• Divide chermoula lentils and couscous between
bowls. Top with caramelised onion.
• Drizzle over tahini garlic sauce. Tear over herbs
and garnish with almonds.
• Squeeze over some lemon juice and serve with
any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!